#########################################################################
# Funciones anova
anova1 <- function(lm){
  a = anova(lm)
  rbind(a,"Total"=c(n,sum(a[2]),NA,NA,NA))
}
anova2 <- function(lm){
  a = car::Anova(lm)
  rbind(a,"Total"=c(sum(a[1]),n,NA,NA))
}
anova3 <- function(lm){
  a = car::Anova(lm,type=3)
  rbind(a,"Total"=c(sum(a[1]),n,NA,NA))
}

# se trabaja con Decathlon y se extraen dos componentes principales
library(FactoMineR)
decathlon = read.csv("Decathlon_cpl.csv",header=TRUE,row.names = 1)
dec = decathlon[14:41,1:10]
attach(dec)
points = decathlon[14:41,11]
n = dim(dec)[1]
dec.pca = PCA(dec,graph=FALSE)
v1 = dec.pca$ind$coord[,1]
v2 = dec.pca$ind$coord[,4]
#########################################################################

SStc = sum((points-mean(points))^2); print(paste("Suma de cuadrados centrados = ",SStc, sep=""))
